<t>
<field>DX.EVENT.TYPE</field>
<desc>
            <p>This table holds the details of activities that may take place during the life of the contract and these will be used for updating related records like accounting, deliveries and transaction activity record.</p>
            <p>      the activities are:</p>
            <p>      AR Contract Assignment Reversal</p>
            <p>      AS Contract Assignment</p>
            <p>      CI contract inception</p>
            <p>      CC Cancellation of contract</p>
            <p>      CD Deletion of contract</p>
            <p>      CU Unauthorised contract amendment</p>
            <p>      CA Contract amendment</p>
            <p>      CM contract maturity</p>
            <p>      CP  Corporate Action</p>
            <p>      CR Contract reversal</p>
            <p>      CS contract settlement (close out)</p>
            <p>      CX Corporate Action Reversal</p>
            <p>      EX Contract Exercise</p>
            <p>      ER Contract Exercise Reversal</p>
            <p>      PP premium posting</p>
            <p>      FC commission positing</p>
            <p>      FE execution fee posting</p>
            <p>      FR regulatory fee positing</p>
            <p>      FL clearing fee posting</p>
            <p>      FM Miscellanous fee posting</p>
            <p>      TT tax positing TRADE</p>
            <p>      PO open position</p>
            <p>      PC close position</p>
            <p>      RP Realised P&amp;L TRADE</p>
            <p>      UP Unrealised P&amp;L</p>
            <p>      UO Unrealised open value</p>
            <p>      IM Initial margin</p>
            <p>      VM variation margin</p>
            <p>      XP  Contract Expiry</p>
            <p>      XR  Contract Expiry Reversal</p>
            <p>
                <p>Validation Rules:</p>
            </p>
            <p />
            <p />
            <p>      two alphabets. predefined with activity.</p>
        </desc>
</t>
